================================
Raspberry Pi Driver for TM1640
================================

:Author: FuryFire
:Version: 0.1


---------------
Intro
---------------
Userland driver for 16x7segment LED display. 
sku.104311 - http://dx.com/p/jy-mcu-16x-digital-tube-yellow-led-module-104311?Utm_rid=58973692

.. image:: http://img.dxcdn.com/productimages/sku_104311_3.jpg

Build on data from 
- http://tronixstuff.wordpress.com/2012/04/09/arduino-and-tm1640-led-display-modules/
- Datasheet
- http://code.google.com/p/tm1638-library/


---------------
Installation
---------------
You will need Gordon's excelent wiringPi library.
https://projects.drogon.net/raspberry-pi/wiringpi/
Install it according to the instructions on the site

Then you need to build the TM1640 driver.


::

> sudo apt-get install build-essential 
> make
> sudo make install


----------------------
Usage
----------------------
Connect the display to the GPIO pins - I will use the wiringPi pin numbering scheme.
https://projects.drogon.net/raspberry-pi/wiringpi/pins/

- VND goes to header #2   (5V)
- GND goes to header #6   (0V)
- DIN goes to header #11  (GPIO2)
- SCLK goes to header #12 (GPIO1)

Run the tool as root
::

> sudo tm1640
> sudo tm1640 on 1
> sudo tm1640 clear
> sudo tm1640 display 0 "123456789012345"

-----------------------
Fonts customization
-----------------------
Fonts are defined in src/fonts.h you will need to recompile the project with /make/ in other to apply changes.
It consist of a 2 dimensional table. First columm representing the ASCII value for the charecter. And the second value defining the LED pattern for that charecter. 
Unsupported charecters are simply set to a space. 
Dots are automatically added to the previous segment so you just pass floats as plain strings. "14.2" will as such only use 3 fields and not 4.

- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seven-segment_display
- http://www.asciitable.com/
- http://www.uize.com/examples/seven-segment-display.html (Use the value listed under GFEDCBA)